Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity => {
            // App losing focus / partially backgrounded
        })
        .OnStop(activity => {
            // App fully backgrounded
        }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app => {
            // App fully backgrounded
        }));
#endif
});
```

**Key points:**

- **Android `OnPause`** = lost focus (maps to `Window.Deactivated`); **`OnStop`** = fully hidden (maps to `Window.Stopped`). iOS `DidEnterBackground` maps to `Window.Stopped`.
- If you don't need platform-specific APIs, you can use the cross-platform `Window.Stopped` event instead — it fires on both platforms when the app backgrounds.
- Keep handlers fast (<2s) to avoid ANR on Android or watchdog kills on iOS.
- On Android, the back button can skip `OnStop` entirely and go straight to `OnDestroy`, so also handle `OnDestroy` if saving critical state.
